text.tspan: Probability is measuring likelihood of events
Def. Event Space: All of the possible outcomes in a model
Ex) Tossing a coin, Event Space = {Head, Tails}
Ex) What's the probability that it's cloudy in Seattle on any given day?
Event Space = {Cloudy, Sunny and beutiful, Sunny and hazy}
Ex) Event space = {Ursinus students in 300/400 CS courses F2021}
P(A or B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A And B)
Ex) Event Space = {All CS students in PA}
